Members of the Limpopo Hawks are currently on the scene at a spares shop in Louis Trichardt where explosives were allegedly found during an operation earlier today (Thursday). Hawks Spokesperson Matimaba Maluleke indicated they had allegedly found explosives which include flare tips, a rifle grenade, three green and three red signal cartridges, a R1 rifle magazine and R5 ammunition. The suspect is to be charged for unlawful possession of explosives and ammunition and will appear in the Louis Trichardt Magistrate&#8217;s Court soon. Story: RC Myburgh &gt;&gt;rc.observer@gmail.com &nbsp;